{"name":"Canoloth","type":"npc","img":"https://5etools-mirror-1.github.io/img/bestiary/MTF/Canoloth.jpg","data":{"abilities":{"str":{"value":18,"proficient":0,"mod":4},"dex":{"value":10,"proficient":0,"mod":0},"con":{"value":17,"proficient":0,"mod":3},"int":{"value":5,"proficient":0,"mod":-3},"wis":{"value":17,"proficient":0,"mod":3},"cha":{"value":12,"proficient":0,"mod":1}},"attributes":{"ac":{"flat":null,"calc":"custom","formula":"@attributes.ac.base + @abilities.dex.mod +6","min":0,"value":null},"hp":{"value":120,"min":0,"max":120,"temp":0,"tempmax":0,"formula":"16d8 + 48"},"init":{"value":0,"bonus":0,"mod":0,"total":0,"prof":0},"movement":{"burrow":null,"climb":null,"fly":null,"swim":null,"walk":50,"units":"ft","hover":false},"senses":{"darkvision":60,"blindsight":0,"tremorsense":0,"truesight":120,"units":"ft","special":""},"spellcasting":"","prof":3,"spelldc":8},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\"><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p class=\"rd__quote-line rd__quote-line--last\">“<i>Canoloths are fundamentally lazy creatures. Given no reason to attack, they rarely rise to the bait.</i>”</p><p><span class=\"rd__quote-by\">— Mordenkainen</span></p><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"3379\"> <span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\">Canoloth.</span></span> <p>Canoloths prefer to enter into contracts to guard valuable treasures and important locations. They always do exactly as asked—never any more, never any less.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>With senses sharp enough to pinpoint the locations of nearby invisible creatures, canoloths respond unfailingly to any threat to their charges. Furthermore, they emit a magical distortion field that prevents creatures close to them from teleporting.</p><p>Canoloths confront intruders with swift and terrible force, projecting long, spiny tongues to grab their foes and drag them close. What happens next depends on the contract. Unless instructed to kill, a canoloth merely holds onto its prisoner, but if given the order to do so, it tears its prey limb from limb.</p></div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"3380\"> <span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\">Yugoloths.</span></span> <p>Mercenaries that ply their trade throughout the Lower Planes and in other realms, yugoloths have a reputation for effectiveness that is matched only by their desire for ever more wealth. Although yugoloths aren't especially loyal and typically try to exploit every potential loophole in a contract, they undertake any task for which they are hired, no matter how despicable. Yugoloths come in a wide variety of forms, including those described in the <a href=\"https://5etools-mirror-1.github.io/bestiary.html#blankhash,flstsource:mm=1,flsttag:yugoloth=1\">Monster Manual</a> and the six creatures presented <a href=\"https://5etools-mirror-1.github.io/bestiary.html#blankhash,flstsource:mtf=1,flsttag:yugoloth=1\">here</a>.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div></div></div>","public":""},"alignment":"neutral evil","race":"","type":{"value":"fiend","subtype":"yugoloth","swarm":null,"custom":""},"environment":"Coastal, Underdark, Urban","cr":8,"spellLevel":0,"xp":{"value":3900},"source":"MTF","class":{}},"traits":{"size":"med","di":{"value":["acid","poison"],"custom":""},"dr":{"value":["cold","fire","lightning","physical"],"custom":""},"dv":{"value":[],"custom":""},"ci":{"value":["poisoned"],"custom":""},"languages":{"value":["abyssal","infernal","custom"],"custom":"telepathy 60 ft."}},"currency":{"pp":0,"gp":0,"ep":0,"sp":0,"cp":0},"skills":{"acr":{"value":0,"ability":"dex","mod":0,"bonus":0,"passive":10},"ani":{"value":0,"ability":"wis","mod":3,"bonus":0,"passive":13},"arc":{"value":0,"ability":"int","mod":-3,"bonus":0,"passive":7},"ath":{"value":0,"ability":"str","mod":4,"bonus":0,"passive":14},"dec":{"value":0,"ability":"cha","mod":1,"bonus":0,"passive":11},"his":{"